Package algorithms.util

Class NodeMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • gnu.trove.impl.hash.THash
      • gnu.trove.impl.hash.TPrimitiveHash
        • gnu.trove.impl.hash.TLongIntHash
          • algorithms.util.NodeMap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Externalizable, java.io.Serializable
    public class NodeMap
extends gnu.trove.impl.hash.TLongIntHash
implements java.io.Externalizable
    An open addressed Map implementation for long keys and long, long, long, int, int, int values. Note that the structure was built specifically to hold fields for a tree node, so there are special rules used to help define that a value has not been set. The key is the unique key for an entry. parent is LONG.MIN_VALUE when not used. left is LONG.MIN_VALUE when not used. right is LONG.MIN_VALUE when not used. value, as soon as the entry exists, always has a used value. color, as soon as the entry exists, always has a used value. size, as soon as the entry exists, always has a used value. Note that equals and hashcode use key and value only.

      • NodeMap

        public NodeMap​(long[] keys,
               long[] parents,
               long[] lefts,
               long[] rights,
               int[] values,
               int[] colors,
               int[] sizes)
        Creates a new TLongLongHashMap instance containing all of the entries in the map passed in. *
        Parameters:
        keys - a long array containing the keys for the matching values.
        parents - is long array containing the first entry of values. For trees using this class, this is the parent field. Note that the backing array has a LONG.MIN_VALUE when the key has no parent.
        lefts - is long array containing the second entry of values. For trees using this class, this is the left field. Note that the backing array has a LONG.MIN_VALUE when the key has no parent.
        rights - is long array containing the third entry of values. For trees using this class, this is the right field. Note that the backing array has a LONG.MIN_VALUE when the key has no parent.
        values - is int array containing the fourth entry of values. For trees using this class, this is the standard value field. Note that the backing array should always have a valid value for this field, that is, if containsKey(key) is true, this value will be fetched and not checked for a null entry like the long fields.
        colors - is int array containing the fourth entry of values. For trees using this class, this is the color value field. Note that the backing array should always have a valid value for this field, that is, if containsKey(key) is true, this value will be fetched and not checked for a null entry like the long fields.
        sizes - int array containing the fourth entry of values. For trees using this class, this is the size value field holding the size of the subtree of this node. Note that the backing array should always have a valid value for this field, that is, if containsKey(key) is true, this value will be fetched and not checked for a null entry like the long fields.
